r food, and give some males an opportunity to increase their breeding success. We suggest that the environment, and its effects on resource distribution, thus determine social structure, which in turn determines the mating pattern that has evolved.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Angell, Ruth L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Butlin, Roger K.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Altringham, John D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fenton, Brock", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/e7bdb2d4aa0997b65eab9e83bc8161c3", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/e30c0f8e5667d93fb595030e244a4e24ef0054c213accd7e6121f8ad820a56dc", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/5G88LMF9", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/5G88LMF9", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6269070b3969f1153d69b3a5f0321451!/b32162-34625", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "e54194", "title": "PLoS ONE", "volume": "8"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/e7bdb2d4aa0997b65eab9e83bc8161c3"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:5G88LMF9"}, {"identifier": "10.1371/journal.pone.0054194"}], "communities": [{"id": "biosyslit"}, {